WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.963 --> 00:00:04.879
The volume of data
within and outside of companies

00:00:04.954 --> 00:00:06.259
has never been greater.

00:00:07.302 --> 00:00:10.905
Professionals who are able 
to turn data into intelligence

00:00:10.980 --> 00:00:13.939
are in high demand
in the market.

00:00:14.344 --> 00:00:15.827
Udacity has created a course

00:00:15.902 --> 00:00:18.207
so that you can gain
all the knowledge needed

00:00:18.324 --> 00:00:20.261
to make data-driven
decisions.

00:00:20.336 --> 00:00:22.365
You will learn
the fundamental concepts

00:00:22.440 --> 00:00:24.498
of data gathering, treatment,
and visualization

00:00:24.573 --> 00:00:26.613
and use these information
for your benefit.

00:00:26.688 --> 00:00:28.041
You'll also be able

00:00:28.116 --> 00:00:30.316
to reveal trends,
foresee demands,

00:00:30.391 --> 00:00:31.691
express correlations

00:00:31.766 --> 00:00:33.849
and simplify the understanding
of huge volumes of data

00:00:33.966 --> 00:00:35.344
for everyone.

00:00:35.681 --> 00:00:38.097
These skills
have become so essential

00:00:38.352 --> 00:00:41.691
that companies such as Airbnb
have already directed their efforts

00:00:41.799 --> 00:00:44.687
towards educating their entire 
teams in Data Science.

00:00:44.762 --> 00:00:47.082
The Data Science Foundations II
Nanodegree program

00:00:47.157 --> 00:00:48.827
was created
by partner companies

00:00:48.944 --> 00:00:51.178
who boast expertise
in Data Science.

00:00:51.253 --> 00:00:53.294
You'll learn quickly

00:00:53.369 --> 00:00:56.083
things like Statistics, Big Data,
R Programming,

00:00:56.200 --> 00:00:57.798
predictive models and more.

00:00:58.241 --> 00:01:00.442
The course also has
special participation

00:01:00.517 --> 00:01:03.708
of Data Scientists from 
Google, Twitter and Netflix

00:01:03.783 --> 00:01:06.457
who can illustrate concepts
with their experience.

00:01:06.532 --> 00:01:09.243
You'll also learn to use
data visualization

00:01:09.318 --> 00:01:12.095
to communicate your insights,
tell stories,

00:01:12.212 --> 00:01:14.577
and you'll see that
it's a very powerful tool

00:01:14.652 --> 00:01:16.046
to explore your data.

00:01:16.121 --> 00:01:18.526
What's cool is that you'll apply
everything you've learned

00:01:18.601 --> 00:01:20.026
to two real projects.

00:01:20.189 --> 00:01:23.792
These projects will be reviewed
by Data Science Specialists

00:01:23.867 --> 00:01:26.658
who will give valuable feedback
for your development.

00:01:26.733 --> 00:01:28.337
And all this practical knowledge

00:01:28.412 --> 00:01:30.487
will make a real difference
in your career.

00:01:30.604 --> 00:01:33.280
Master the basic
Data Science concepts

00:01:33.355 --> 00:01:35.417
and make
more effective decisions.

00:01:35.580 --> 00:01:38.639
Sign up for the
Data Science Foundations II Nanodegree

00:01:38.714 --> 00:01:41.486
and take another step
in your Data Science,

00:01:41.561 --> 00:01:44.088
Machine Learning
and Artificial Intelligence career.

